dor Hundredfist</a> -- 52nd Disciple ~ Soldiers of Destiny</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umuoftunare.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mu of Tunare</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br>  Posts: 536<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/13/02 9:02:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11418.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Possible equipment upgrades, on limited budget  =\</span><hr size=1> How much money do you have to spend?<br><br>Do you have a tailor in your guild?<br><br>Acrylia Reinforced armor is nice.  You could replace both bracers shoulder and legs with Acrylia Re armor that wouldnt be too much especially if you know a tailor.  <br><br>I might try and trade the mushroom viel for Crystal Spider Eyes or Clattering bone necklace. <br><br>At 52 you could group in Maidens Eye and get some no drop shrouded boots that drop often better than yours also could get GSC wich is better than Wu's.<br><br> <p><A HREF=http://http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=78811>Brother Poppso</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulizzardlee.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lizzardlee</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br>  Posts: 513<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/13/02 10:15:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11418.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Possible equipment upgrades, on limited budget  =\</span><hr size=1> Does your guild do Kael? If so just upgrade your slots with thurg quest armor. If you had plat could do better but thurg ain't bad. <br><br>Edit: Oh even better ideas read below:<br><br><br>Get some guild groups together and hunt for this stuff:<br><br>The Grey has to offer you:<br>Grey Flesh Arms, Tunic, Clattering Bone Necklace, and shissar headband.<br><br>Kael:<br>Thurg quest armor<br><br>Old Seb:<br>Disco drops IFS if I remember right<br><br>Burning Wood:<br>Wurmscale Coat<br><br>Velks:<br>Spider Crystal Eyes(not sure what drops this though... drops IN velks but off of what I'm not sure)<br><br>Lower Guk:<br>Froggy Crown<br><br>Waking Lands:<br>Bracers of Benevolence(quested)<br><br>I'd Start with the grey see if you can get a guild group or 2 with a tracker and hunt named. Alot of goodies drop here. Bone Handled Scimatar and that wis sheild will get the druids and clerics commin heh. Also you have a decent guild with lots of 50+ get a group together and get your pipes and do your epic boy! Your doing better than me on the epic. *grumble dang raster /cry*<br> <p>52 Disciple of Cazic Thule - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=87708">Lizzardlee Blitzfizt</a><br>Erollisi Marr</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulizzardlee.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lizzardlee</A> at: 9/13/02 10:28:29 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uillydth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Illydth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/13/02 10:23:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11418.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Possible equipment upgrades, on limited budget  =\</span><hr size=1> As to Maidens Eye, you could always do the typical monk begging thing.<br><br>Drop up to Maidens Eye, FD and throw yourself on the mercy of the 50+'s up there for a GSC.  I'm using one right now and it's really sweet.  I&quot;ll end up replacing it soon, but it'll last me up through 40 or so.  Theoretically you could go get one at about 14th or 15th when you get FD...that's really all you need...that and alot of pacience. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umackdaddymonky.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MackDaddyMonky</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 243<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/13/02 10:27:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11418.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Possible equipment upgrades, on limited budget  =\</span><hr size=1> FYI monks get FD at lvl 17.<br>:P <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=289142" target="_blank"><img src="http://ourhaven.50megs.com/images/abbyt-sig2.jpg" border="0"></a> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ucromulent357.showPublicProfile?language=EN>cromulent357</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 161<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/13/02 11:51:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11418.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Possible equipment upgrades, on limited budget  =\</span><hr size=1> Yeah get on as many kael raids you can, preferably your guild's raids, cuz you get stuff by merit. <br><br>Sceptre of mastery - nice monk only no drop 1hb<br>helm of tallon/vallon - nice head piece<br>various kael armor drops<br>belt of contention drops there too i think.<br><br>acrylia armor is decent for monk. kinda cheap, at least cheaper than panther skin. I still have acrylia shoulder. Still looking for those damn chokidai pauldrons thingies <p><p align=center><b>Cromulent Mcgarnacle</b><Br><b>60 Grandmaster Monk</b><Br><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=144144>Inspect My Dingleberries!!</a><Br><a href=http://www.dbguild.net>Dragonsbane Elite</a></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usanaldor31.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sanaldor31</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/13/02 1:36:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11418.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Possible equipment upgrades, on limited budget  =\</span><hr size=1> Someone's putting together a Kael raid for tomorrow afternoon, and I plan on attending.  My main goal is the Scepter of Mastery, but that's only feasible if we get a good turnout.  I'd rather not try taking down Bjrakor with anything less than 2 full groups.  Also interested in Kael for Coldain/CoV faction.<br><br>As for the Grey, I'm still looking for an unlimited/clicky EB item I could get... we have a couple Umbral Plains raids/gatherings scheduled, and I'd rather not die in the Grey on the way there when my EB runs out.<br><br>Maiden's Eye is definitely a possibility... don't know the zone at all, but it seems my higher-level guildies are always there.<br><br>Sebilis is probably not the place for me... at least, not until I'm a god-monk and people actually want me in their group.  It's possible for a lvl 52 to group there successfully, but only if you bring your own group with you (at least, that's the way it seems to me).  The level 60 epic SK/Warrior sitting next to me will always be picked over the lowly non-epic, pre-55 monk, even for pulling purposes.  I can wait to go back to Sebilis... maybe when I'm around lvl 56 with AA points and people start taking me seriously.<br><br>As for my available plat, I'm dead broke, almost.  I do have a tailor in the guild, but even if he'd make me some armor at cost, it would probably be too much (though I'm not sure what the components for Reinforced Acrylia armor cost, or even what they are).  I'm still trying to find a good place to solo for cash, too.  I can take seafuries with a partner, but then I'm still sharing the loot.<br><br>Well, I just got off work, and I'm anxious to get in-game and see what my guild's up to.  Thanks for the suggestions. <p><p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=88424 target=_blank>Sanaldor Hundredfist</a> -- 52nd Disciple ~ Soldiers of Destiny</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulizzardlee.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lizzardlee</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br>  Posts: 516<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(9/13/02 4:59:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11418.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Possible equipment upgrades, on limited budget  =\</span><hr size=1> Get a group in the grey again for EB item. Drag a druid along for casty EB till you get shissar organs(3 or 4 of them I beleive) and turn them in to a npc in Katta for a EB necklace. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p>52 Disciple of Cazic Thule - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=87708">Lizzardlee Blitzfizt</a><br>Erollisi Marr</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table 